{"id":89258,"title":"[Physical rehabilitation in extensively burned patients].","abstract":"The rehabilitation of the extensively burned patient aims to prevent and minimize consequences of the own lesion this is supported by three pillars: 1) postural treatment to prevent contractures; 2) kinesiotherapy to maintain/restore joint range of movement and muscle strength; 3) functional recovery. Physical therapy is essential in the multidisciplinary team. A coordinated team assures better results and positively influences the quality of life of the patients.","date":"2014-04-17","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24738174","annotations":[{"name":"Physical therapy","weight":0.823443,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physical_therapy"},{"name":"Quality of life","weight":0.816331,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quality_of_life"},{"name":"Muscle","weight":0.789254,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muscle"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.738937,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Burn","weight":0.703547,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burn"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.701843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Lesion","weight":0.633497,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesion"},{"name":"Joint","weight":0.63229,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joint"},{"name":"Kinesiotherapy","weight":0.566667,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kinesiotherapy"},{"name":"Contracture","weight":0.18915,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contracture"},{"name":"Range of motion","weight":0.186121,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Range_of_motion"},{"name":"Human positions","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_positions"},{"name":"Multidisciplinarity","weight":0.0377168,"wikipedia_article":"http:/